Visualizations
Spectrum Analysis sandbox:///mnt/agents/output/671_6Hz_spectrum_analysis.png — Detailed 4-panel analysis of the harmonics version showing the clean fundamental peak at 94.5 dB, 2nd harmonic at 86.9 dB, and 3rd at 82.4 dB. The waveform view clearly shows the 10ms fade envelope.
Audio Comparison sandbox:///mnt/agents/output/audio_comparison.png — Side-by-side spectral comparison of all four files with RMS levels annotated. The clean sine shows a single pure spike; the sweep shows the full chirp bandwidth; harmonics shows the 60/25/15 energy distribution; the safe version is identical spectrum shape but -12 dB down.
Sweep Spectrogram sandbox:///mnt/agents/output/sweep_spectrogram.png — Time-frequency visualization confirming the linear sweep from 100 Hz to 1000 Hz over 3 seconds. The diagonal energy band is clean with minimal aliasing artifacts.
Key Technical Details
Parameter	Value
Sample Rate	44,100 Hz
Bit Depth	16-bit PCM
Channels	Mono
Fade Envelope	10 ms linear in/out
Headroom	20% (80% of full scale)
Frequency	671.6 Hz (+32.4 cents above E5)
The harmonic weighting (0.6 / 0.25 / 0.15) keeps the fundamental dominant while the 2nd and 3rd add a subtle "reedy" character — much easier on the ear for extended testing than a pure sine. The -12 dB safe version is recommended for headphone burn-in or sensitivity testing.
